    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-09-15T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-09-15T23:00:00-05:00" n="568"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d568">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12146: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow (<persName
                            corresp="frus1932v03#p_AWA1" type="from">Adams</persName>) to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-16T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >September 16, 1932—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received September 16—5:10
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>87. 1. Government troops now occupy Pailochi, Low Point and Chuho. The main body
                    of communist troops in central Hupeh are reliably reported entirely surprised by
                    Government troops in the Red Lake region.</p>
                <p>2. The National Flood Relief Commission engineers who were taken as hostages by
                    the Communists in connection with <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_BCC1"
                        >Baker</persName>’s release have now been rescued. The <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_BCC1">Baker</persName> case may therefore now be
                    considered as closed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_AWA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Adams</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
